The paper deals with geolocation estimation using text data from Twitter. This falls under the domain of natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR), which are covered by cs.CL and cs.IR sub-categories. The proposed method involves the use of neural networks, which is a common technique in machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL), covered by cs.LG. The paper also involves image processing techniques, specifically convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which are covered by cs.CV. Finally, the paper deals with probability distributions and density estimation, which are covered by cs.SI.
